  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>basmati rice</strong> and 300ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p>\r\n<p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p>\r\n<p>Once cooked, remove from the heat and keep covered until serving</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-pork-and-portobello-stroganoff/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced pork</strong> and cook for 1-2 min or until golden</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-pork-and-portobello-stroganoff/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p>\r\n<p>Peel and finely slice the <strong>brown&nbsp;onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>Slice the <strong>portobello mushrooms</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-pork-and-portobello-stroganoff/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the <strong>pork</strong> is brown, transfer it to a bowl and return the pan to a medium heat with a knob of <strong>butter</strong></p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>sliced onion</strong> and <strong>mushroom</strong> and cook for 6-7 min or until starting to caramelise</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>balsamic vinegar</strong>&nbsp;and cook for 1 min further</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-pork-and-portobello-stroganoff/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile,&nbsp;dissolve the <strong>beef stock cube<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> and<strong> tomato paste</strong> in 175ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[350ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>smoked paprika</strong>&nbsp;and <strong>beef stock</strong> to the pan and cook for 3-4 min or until thickened&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-pork-and-portobello-stroganoff/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop the <strong>parsley</strong> finely, including the stalks</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-pork-and-portobello-stroganoff/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the sauce has thickened, add the <strong>clotted cream</strong>,&nbsp;<strong>Dijon mustard </strong>and<strong> browned pork </strong>and cook for 2-3 min or until the<strong> pork </strong>is cooked through and the sauce is thick and glossy<strong>&nbsp;</strong>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-pork-and-portobello-stroganoff/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>pork &amp; portobello stroganoff</strong> over the <strong>rice</strong></p>\r\n<p>Garnish with the <strong>chopped parsley</strong></p>\r\n<p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
